The paper is about a tool for debugging neural machine translation systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of attention weights, which is a common technique in deep learning and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI the second likely sub-category. The tool is designed to help researchers and developers improve their NMT systems, which involves training and optimizing models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the comparison of translation outputs from different NMT engines or experiments, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper includes examples of good and bad translations, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
